                     ). The discharge curve of equilibrium potential (E

                        eq
                     ) is then extrapolated towards zero current in order to obtained the overpotential heat generation curve based on the discharge current of the cell. The result showed a good agreement to the discharge curves that were obtained experimentally. Likewise, with the finding of cell voltage (E), current (I) and temperature (T) that were obtained experimentally, the thermal behavior of the cell in respect of its internal temperature is predicted and represented by comparing both the simulated and experimental cell internal temperatures.
